info.headline: Flood Advisory issued September 08 at 3:34PM EDT until September 08 at 7:30PM EDT by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 545 PM EDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues. * WHERE...Portions of central New Jersey...and southern New Jersey... including the following counties...in central New Jersey... Monmouth. In southern New Jersey...Ocean. * WHEN...Until 545 PM EDT. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 333 PM EDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly across portions of the advisory area. Between 1 and 2.5 inches of rain have fallen. - Some locations that may experience flooding include... Lakewood, Jackson, Howell, Marlboro, Tinton Falls, Holmdel, Farmingdale, Adelphia, Freewood Acres, East Freehold, West Freehold, and Vista Center. - This includes the following highways... Interstate 195 in New Jersey between mile markers 21 and 31. Garden State Parkway between mile markers 113 and 114. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
